just can't get enough ♪

01:09.375 --> 01:11.834
Last time.
Five, six, seven, eight.

01:11.834 --> 01:15.250
♪ Oh oh oh oh
oh oh oh oh ♪

01:15.250 --> 01:16.542
♪ Just can't get
just can't get enough ♪

01:16.542 --> 01:20.417
Shake it.
Seven. Good. Pa-da-da.

01:20.417 --> 01:23.041
♪ T-O-U-C-H
You're hot to touch ♪

01:23.041 --> 01:25.875
♪ Touch by the way
that we shake hey ♪

01:25.875 --> 01:27.458
♪ H-O-T T-O ♪

01:27.458 --> 01:29.959
♪ T-O-U-C-H
You're hot to touch ♪

01:29.959 --> 01:32.875
♪ Touch by the way
that we shake hey ♪♪

01:32.875 --> 01:34.708
[cheering]

01:36.083 --> 01:38.250
Oh, that's a good track
right there.

01:38.250 --> 01:39.959
- Who is that?
- Some new band.

01:39.959 --> 01:41.417
- Werewolf vs. Unicorn.
- Oh.

01:41.417 --> 01:42.583
- 'They play locally.'
- Alice found them.

01:42.583 --> 01:44.750
Yeah, it's pretty good.

01:44.750 --> 01:45.708
"Pretty good?"

01:46.750 --> 01:47.917
Very good?

01:47.917 --> 01:49.417
It's awesome.

01:49.417 --> 01:51.708
Werewolf vs. Unicorn
plays all the clubs.

01:51.708 --> 01:53.708
I tracked down their
bassist, chatted him up

01:53.708 --> 01:55.375
bought him some drinks,
and scored our new song.

01:55.375 --> 01:58.083
It's exclusive and unknown,
which makes it special.

01:58.083 --> 01:59.792
Yeah, a fresh song
could give us the edge

01:59.792 --> 02:01.250
that we need at Nationals.

02:01.250 --> 02:02.917
Last year, Tennessee
and Fort Hill lost

02:02.917 --> 02:05.583
because both squads
used the same Li'l Kim song.

02:05.583 --> 02:08.000
Why would they use
any Li'l Kim song?

02:08.000 --> 02:10.458
Don't be a hater, Marti.

02:10.458 --> 02:12.875
Fine. Whatever.
I defer to my captain.

02:15.458 --> 02:17.625
- Oh, can I--
- Can I see...

02:17.625 --> 02:21.041
Oh. You...

02:21.041 --> 02:22.834
I think it's me.

02:26.583 --> 02:28.625
I wanted you to be
the first to know.

02:28.625 --> 02:30.959
Look what just showed
up in my mailbox.

02:37.375 --> 02:38.667
[chuckles]

02:38.667 --> 02:40.333
This is fantastic.

02:40.333 --> 02:42.625
Fantastic,
and a little confusing.

02:42.625 --> 02:44.000
Why did you apply to Lancer?

02:44.000 --> 02:46.125
Oh, I filled out
an application last year

02:46.125 --> 02:49.667
in a moment
of vocational crisis.

02:49.667 --> 02:51.166
Why is this the first time
I'm hearing of it?

02:51.166 --> 02:53.166
I got wait-listed
the first time, you know.

02:53.166 --> 02:56.000
I rolled the application
over this year and...

02:56.000 --> 02:57.834
I don't know, I figured
I'd wait to see how I did

02:57.834 --> 03:01.500
before I started
advertising it. What?

03:01.500 --> 03:03.041
It's not every day
I get to see you insecure

03:03.041 --> 03:05.750
about something. I mean,
give me a moment to enjoy it.

03:07.166 --> 03:08.875
- You done?
- Not yet, no.

03:08.875 --> 03:10.291
Okay.

03:11.625 --> 03:14.166
Okay, now I'm done.

03:14.166 --> 03:16.333
Hm, I'm really proud of you.

03:16.333 --> 03:18.834
- So what's your major gonna be?
- Film, you know.

03:18.834 --> 03:21.041
I mean, assuming
I get into the program.

03:21.041 --> 03:22.625
Well, I thought
you said you were in.

03:22.625 --> 03:23.667
Well, I'm into the university.

03:23.667 --> 03:24.834
The film school

03:24.834 --> 03:25.834
has an entirely separate

03:25.834 --> 03:27.333
application process, you know.

03:27.333 --> 03:29.333
I gotta...do an interview

03:29.333 --> 03:32.000
write a ton of essays,
and make a short film.

03:32.000 --> 03:33.667
Oh, wow.

03:33.667 --> 03:35.875
But, you know, if I don't
get in I got my fallback...

03:35.875 --> 03:38.708
...all worked out.
I'll just become a Hellcat.

03:39.875 --> 03:41.083
- You'll become a what?
- Yeah.

03:41.083 --> 03:43.208
I figure
I'll, I'll be a base.

03:43.208 --> 03:44.875
I'll be your base.

03:44.875 --> 03:46.500
I mean, I-I can count on you
to get me on the squad.

03:46.500 --> 03:48.750
- I-I don't know if I could--
- Wink-wink.

03:48.750 --> 03:51.834
- You pull a few strings and--
- I can't, like...

03:51.834 --> 03:54.875
- I'm joking.
- Right.

03:54.875 --> 03:57.041
- Yeah, I totally knew.
- You didn't.

03:57.041 --> 03:58.375
No, I didn't.

03:58.375 --> 03:59.583
But please don't joke
about cheerleading.

03:59.583 --> 04:01.041
It gives me a nervous stomach.

04:02.041 --> 04:03.875
[humming]

04:05.041 --> 04:07.708
- Hey.
- Hey.

04:07.708 --> 04:12.458
♪ Born on Halloween
born on Halloween ♪

04:12.458 --> 04:14.708
♪ Bless the Lord
with a G chord ♪

04:14.708 --> 04:17.875
♪ I was born on Halloween ♪♪

04:17.875 --> 04:20.750
Do you recognize this?

04:20.750 --> 04:22.583
No. I like it. You write it?

04:22.583 --> 04:24.917
Oh, you disappoint me.
Here, listen, listen, listen.

04:24.917 --> 04:27.750
♪ Benjamin Franklin
flew that kite out there ♪

04:27.750 --> 04:29.625
♪ In the middle of the storm ♪

04:29.625 --> 04:31.917
♪ Abraham Lincoln
grew his beard ♪

04:31.917 --> 04:34.542
♪ To keep Mrs. Lincoln warm ♪

04:34.542 --> 04:36.875
♪ Edison turned the lights on ♪

04:36.875 --> 04:39.375
♪ It must have been
a hell of a scene ♪

04:39.375 --> 04:41.625
♪ I was raised by wolves ♪

04:41.625 --> 04:44.834
♪ I was born on Halloween ♪

04:44.834 --> 04:47.250
[chuckles]

04:47.250 --> 04:49.083
It's one of your dad's.

04:49.083 --> 04:50.375
My dad's what?

04:53.250 --> 04:54.708
Are you saying he wrote that?

04:57.583 --> 04:59.333
Wait, keep-keep playing, please.

04:59.333 --> 05:01.625
- Well, I-I was just trying--
- No, no, Travis, please.

05:01.625 --> 05:04.250
Keep playing. Go.

05:04.250 --> 05:06.917
♪ Born on Halloween ♪

05:06.917 --> 05:09.291
♪ Born on Halloween ♪

05:09.291 --> 05:11.291
♪ Bless the Lord
with a G chord ♪

05:11.291 --> 05:14.959
♪ I was born on Halloween ♪♪

05:14.959 --> 05:16.291
It's...

05:16.291 --> 05:18.834
I...

05:18.834 --> 05:21.667
I had no idea
my dad wrote, wrote songs.

05:21.667 --> 05:24.667
Look, your mom was nice enough
to let me stay here.

05:24.667 --> 05:26.125
I don't wanna get
in the middle of this.

05:26.125 --> 05:28.625
- Where did you get this?
- From your mom.

05:31.083 --> 05:32.625
I had no idea you didn't know

05:32.625 --> 05:34.708
or I wouldn't have
brought it up.

05:34.708 --> 05:36.500
[sighing]

05:36.500 --> 05:37.875
Just...

05:39.667 --> 05:41.166
Just tell me
what you know, please.

05:41.166 --> 05:43.500
Uh...

05:43.500 --> 05:45.458
Last night your mom
and I had some wine

05:45.458 --> 05:48.917
we got to talkin'
about old times and old music

05:48.917 --> 05:51.000
and she went into the bedroom,
she come out with that

05:51.000 --> 05:53.041
and asked me to play it.

05:53.041 --> 05:54.375
That's all I know.

05:55.834 --> 05:57.291
I take it you guys
don't talk about him.

05:57.291 --> 05:58.834
No. No. No.

05:58.834 --> 06:01.333
[scoffs]
And that's-that's
classic Wanda.

06:01.333 --> 06:04.041
I spent my life taking care
of her and I get nothing.

06:04.041 --> 06:06.291
Then you come in here,
you fix the garbage disposal

06:06.291 --> 06:08.375
and suddenly
you're in the inner circle.

06:08.375 --> 06:10.667
Huh!

06:10.667 --> 06:13.000
How is that fair, Travis?

06:13.000 --> 06:15.125
How is that fair, huh?

06:15.125 --> 06:16.500
I think you have
to talk to her about it.

06:16.500 --> 06:18.333
Ah. Insightful.

06:18.333 --> 06:20.667
Yeah, I can, I can see
why she opened up to you.

06:20.667 --> 06:23.041
["Hot To Touch" over stereo]

06:23.041 --> 06:24.583
♪ Just let it go ♪

06:24.583 --> 06:26.375
♪ And feel low ♪

06:26.375 --> 06:30.375
♪ She's hot to touch
can't get enough ♪

06:30.375 --> 06:33.500
- Wait. Why are we stopping?
- Quick detour. Two minutes.

06:33.500 --> 06:37.375
♪ She's hot to touch
in full control ♪♪

06:37.375 --> 06:39.667
I swear, if you make me late
for one more hair appointment--

06:39.667 --> 06:41.125
Two minutes.

06:43.000 --> 06:45.041
Dan can't afford nice
film books, so I wanna give him

06:45.041 --> 06:47.083
all of these to help him study.

06:47.083 --> 06:48.667
Who uses books?

06:48.667 --> 06:51.208
Anything he needs to know
is online. Come on.

06:51.208 --> 06:53.041
Yeah, until technology fails us.

06:53.041 --> 06:54.708
And then you'll be
begging me on your knees

06:54.708 --> 06:56.750
for a glimpse
of my coffee table books.

06:56.750 --> 06:58.291
Your two minutes are up,
by the way.

06:58.291 --> 07:01.125
Hey! I wasn't expecting
to see you till the weekend.

07:01.125 --> 07:02.917
I've got an ultrasound
to show you.

07:02.917 --> 07:04.875
Unh-unh, Charlotte.
Now slowing your sister down.

07:04.875 --> 07:07.458
I saw the heartbeat
and everything.

07:07.458 --> 07:09.792
Doesn't that look
like he's smiling?

07:11.792 --> 07:14.125
I-I think that's his bum.

07:14.125 --> 07:15.583
- Mm. Really?
- Yeah.

07:15.583 --> 07:17.041
Oh, I think you're right.

07:18.625 --> 07:20.291
Are...

07:20.291 --> 07:22.083
Are you having
a party downstairs?

07:22.083 --> 07:25.417
Oh. Now, that's my other news.
We got into Nationals.

07:25.417 --> 07:28.583
How? You were eliminated
at Sectionals.

07:28.583 --> 07:31.125
Burlington got busted
for illegal diet supplements.

07:31.125 --> 07:35.458
- So we're taking their spot.
- Congratulations.

07:35.458 --> 07:38.083
I'm not flying, but I'm still
captain, so some of the girls

07:38.083 --> 07:39.750
'are downstairs
working out a routine.'

07:39.750 --> 07:41.667
- Oh, my God.
- What?

07:41.667 --> 07:43.333
- That song.
- Yeah, it's cool, right?

07:43.333 --> 07:45.959
- It's a local band.
- Werewolf vs. Unicorn. I know.

07:45.959 --> 07:47.959
Since when are you
hip to music?

07:47.959 --> 07:51.834
One, up, two, down, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

07:51.834 --> 07:54.917
One, two, three, four,
five, six...

07:56.417 --> 07:57.917
I hope you're not planning

07:57.917 --> 07:59.959
on using this song
for your routine.

07:59.959 --> 08:02.458
- What do you care?
- It's the Hellcats' song.

08:02.458 --> 08:05.458
Guys, this is bad. We can't use
the same song, not in Nationals.

08:05.458 --> 08:07.125
We have an agreement
with the band.

08:07.125 --> 08:08.834
- So do we.
- Prove it!

08:08.834 --> 08:11.291
- I've got nothing to prove!
- Prove you didn't steal it.

08:11.291 --> 08:12.792
Do you hear that?
She just called us thieves.

08:12.792 --> 08:14.291
I hear outrage, Nasty Kathy.

08:14.291 --> 08:16.458
- But no denial.
- Stop calling me that.

08:16.458 --> 08:17.917
Nasty Kathy.

08:17.917 --> 08:19.625
Keep running your mouth, Alice.
I dare you.

08:19.625 --> 08:21.417
- Or what, piglet?
- Oh, don't test me.

08:21.417 --> 08:23.291
Oh, nasty, Nasty Kathy.

08:23.291 --> 08:25.166
- Everyone calm down.
- You know what?

08:25.166 --> 08:27.208
You out of all people have
no right to tell me what to do.

08:27.208 --> 08:29.667
Neither team can afford
to lose focus, okay.

08:29.667 --> 08:31.333
Battling with each other
is a waste of resources.

08:31.333 --> 08:34.000
And why is that,
because our pyramids are sloppy

08:34.000 --> 08:37.000
and our tumblers are slow?
Oh, no. That's you.

08:37.000 --> 08:38.958
You wanna talk
sloppy stunt work?

08:38.958 --> 08:40.875
Shall we roll video
of one Charlotte Monroe

08:40.875 --> 08:41.958
falling on her head
at qualifiers?

08:41.958 --> 08:43.000
Come on.

08:43.000 --> 08:44.417
Trash talk all you want, Kathy.

08:44.417 --> 08:46.041
but the fact
is you have less lead time

08:46.041 --> 08:47.875
than your competitors,
and you're already down a flyer.

08:47.875 --> 08:48.959
And why are we down a flyer?

08:48.959 --> 08:50.000
Because your sister

08:50.000 --> 08:51.375
got pregs by your ex.

08:51.375 --> 08:52.667
Kathy!

08:54.291 --> 08:55.667
I didn't mean that.

08:57.834 --> 08:59.792
Char?

08:59.792 --> 09:01.667
I-I say stupid things
all the time.

09:01.667 --> 09:02.834
Char!

09:04.875 --> 09:07.250
We should get sandwiches,
I think.

09:07.250 --> 09:09.000
Come on, Nasty Kathy,
I'm sure we can find

09:09.000 --> 09:10.875
some live spiders
for you to eat.

09:10.875 --> 09:13.625
[dramatic music]

09:18.000 --> 09:19.542
It was an accident.

09:19.542 --> 09:21.875
So what, um, you-you
tripped and stumbled

09:21.875 --> 09:25.250
on to my ex-boyfriend's penis?

09:25.250 --> 09:27.250
No wonder you didn't tell
me who the father was.

09:27.250 --> 09:29.208
And everyone else knew, but me.
I mean, what's that about?

09:29.208 --> 09:31.000
I was planning on telling you.

09:31.000 --> 09:33.083
And Nasty Kathy
ruined everything.

09:33.083 --> 09:36.125
Yeah, well, you should've
told me first. Before anyone.

09:36.125 --> 09:37.583
I'm sorry.

09:40.208 --> 09:42.583
Of all the guys
in the world, why Noah?

09:42.583 --> 09:44.417
Don't say it like that.
"Why, Noah?"

09:44.417 --> 09:47.083
Just because he wasn't
good enough for you.

09:47.083 --> 09:49.375
I've liked him
since the sixth grade.

09:49.375 --> 09:50.708
But he was always into you.

09:50.708 --> 09:52.959
I was just the stupid
little sister.

09:52.959 --> 09:54.083
Until he bought you
at that date auction

09:54.083 --> 09:55.583
and you broke his heart.

09:55.583 --> 09:57.208
He came on to me
when I was seeing someone.

09:57.208 --> 10:00.250
Whatever. You gave up
any claim you had to him.

10:00.250 --> 10:03.625
And he was sad,
so...I made my move.

10:03.625 --> 10:05.417
- So you gave him rebound sex?
- God.

10:05.417 --> 10:06.917
You Lancer people
have a little

10:06.917 --> 10:08.417
judgmental term
for everything, don't you?

10:08.417 --> 10:10.291
Okay, I'm sorry,
I'm just trying really hard

10:10.291 --> 10:12.875
to wrap my brain around this.

10:12.875 --> 10:15.250
He showed up at my window.

10:15.250 --> 10:18.792
We stayed up till 6:00 talking
about our lives, our futures.

10:18.792 --> 10:20.959
So this was that same night?

10:20.959 --> 10:23.959
For the first time,
he was paying attention to me.

10:23.959 --> 10:26.458
We fell in love.

10:26.458 --> 10:28.417
And we're getting married.

10:28.417 --> 10:30.834
- When?
- Soon.

10:30.834 --> 10:33.458
We're looking for apartments
as soon as midterms are over.

10:33.458 --> 10:35.625
The Cyclones said they'll
help me decorate the nursery.

10:35.625 --> 10:37.458
And Sandy's sister
has this adorable crib

10:37.458 --> 10:39.375
with adorable matching
furniture.

10:41.291 --> 10:43.500
Does mom know?

10:43.500 --> 10:47.458
She thinks it's the best thing
for the baby.

10:47.458 --> 10:49.125
And me.

10:49.125 --> 10:50.583
And you agree?

10:52.458 --> 10:55.208
- Charlotte, do you agree?
- Of course, I do.

10:57.125 --> 10:58.500
I love Noah.

10:59.250 --> 11:00.875
And he loves me.

11:05.917 --> 11:08.500
(Vanessa)
You won't believe
the day I had.

11:08.500 --> 11:10.834
The cherry was that
the phone call I got

11:10.834 --> 11:12.375
from the Mem-Chris cheer coach?

11:12.375 --> 11:14.250
Apparently, the girls,
they're using

11:14.250 --> 11:16.959
the same piece of music. And now
there's blood on the walls.

11:16.959 --> 11:19.458
[chuckles]
They got in a fight
over a song.

11:19.458 --> 11:20.667
- Really?
- Don't get me started.

11:20.667 --> 11:21.667
And Alice said she's gonna go

11:21.667 --> 11:23.166
talk to the band tonight

11:23.166 --> 11:25.875
to, I quote,
"Flash a little cleavage

11:25.875 --> 11:27.125
and straighten
the whole thing out."

11:27.125 --> 11:28.667
That always worked for me, so...

11:28.667 --> 11:30.125
Yeah, well,
I'll be sure and tell

11:30.125 --> 11:31.875
the new athletic director that.

11:31.875 --> 11:34.041
That's assuming
we even hire one.

11:34.041 --> 11:35.834
The search committee's
been looking.

11:35.834 --> 11:37.458
No one's taking the bait.

11:37.458 --> 11:38.708
Who'd want to be the poor SOB

11:38.708 --> 11:40.375
who has to clean up
Bill Marsh's mess?

11:40.375 --> 11:42.458
You two look like you
could use a refill.

11:42.458 --> 11:45.125
- Thanks, Wanda.
- On the house.

11:45.125 --> 11:47.708
I am so sorry to hear
about you and Derrick.

11:50.041 --> 11:52.041
Oh, how heartbreakin'.

11:52.041 --> 11:54.250
Yeah. It's, uh...

11:54.250 --> 11:56.583
Just thanks.

11:56.583 --> 11:58.708
Would've been
a lovely weddin'.

11:58.708 --> 12:01.708
They were talkin' to me
about doin' the event.

12:01.708 --> 12:04.375
Yeah, it's a shame that we won't
be working together.

12:04.375 --> 12:07.208
Unless, of course, um,
there's another weddin'

12:07.208 --> 12:09.500
comin' down the pike
sometime soon.

12:12.041 --> 12:15.041
No. That won't be
happening anytime soon.

12:15.041 --> 12:17.792
Who knows? I mean, ain't
none of gettin' any younger.

12:20.041 --> 12:22.208
Oh, coach, I put a little
water in that whiskey.

12:22.208 --> 12:23.917
You know, just in case
you're asked to suit up

12:23.917 --> 12:25.875
for the big game later on.

12:28.000 --> 12:29.667
Well, very thoughtful.

12:31.041 --> 12:32.625
We are never coming here again.

12:34.250 --> 12:37.125
Relax, it's just
Wanda being Wanda.

12:39.458 --> 12:42.583
- Don't.
- Okay.

12:42.583 --> 12:45.583
I'm sorry.
I don't wanna be that woman.

12:45.583 --> 12:47.750
Which woman is that exactly?

12:47.750 --> 12:51.125
The heartbreaker.
The bitch. The slut.

12:51.125 --> 12:54.083
Well, if they're so determined
to judge, I say "Let 'em."

12:54.083 --> 12:55.750
Oh, that's easy for you to say.

12:55.750 --> 12:57.917
- Why?
- 'Cause you're a guy.

12:57.917 --> 12:59.291
- Oh, come on.
- Yeah.

12:59.291 --> 13:01.583
Even in this
supposedly enlightened age

13:01.583 --> 13:04.375
there's a double standard.

13:04.375 --> 13:07.083
Don't you find something
new would come between us?

13:07.083 --> 13:09.041
What?

13:09.041 --> 13:10.333
My mom.

13:11.959 --> 13:14.083
She used to always say we, uh...

13:14.083 --> 13:15.792
we all carry around
our own hell with us

13:15.792 --> 13:17.583
like a turtle carries a shell.

13:17.583 --> 13:19.333
Now, I can't speak for you

13:19.333 --> 13:20.917
but, uh,
I've wasted a lot of years

13:20.917 --> 13:22.417
and I've delayed
a lot of happiness.

13:22.417 --> 13:24.417
And I'm not
gonna do it anymore.

13:24.417 --> 13:25.792
Red...

13:29.834 --> 13:31.291
Drop the shell.

13:33.250 --> 13:37.166
I'm sorry.
I have to go.

13:37.166 --> 13:39.875
[instrumental music]

13:43.792 --> 13:45.208
[door opens]

13:47.458 --> 13:49.417
Hey.

13:49.417 --> 13:50.834
Where's Travis?

13:50.834 --> 13:52.625
Brought home
some dead food orders.

13:52.625 --> 13:54.125
I got a couple turkey burgers

13:54.125 --> 13:57.291
and a Greek salad
that looks pretty promisin'.

13:57.291 --> 14:00.500
Travis wanted to give
us some breathing room.

14:00.500 --> 14:03.500
So you and I can have
a little heart-to-heart.

14:03.500 --> 14:04.917
You sound serious.

14:06.708 --> 14:09.667
Why does Travis know things
about dad that I don't know?

14:09.667 --> 14:12.375
And more importantly, why don't
I know dad wrote music?

14:12.375 --> 14:14.625
Oh, I told you
he was a musician.

14:14.625 --> 14:18.625
Yeah, I know he played, I never
knew he actually wrote songs.

14:18.625 --> 14:20.208
You think
I wouldn't be interested?

14:20.208 --> 14:22.667
- Music is my thing.
- Music is one of your things.

14:22.667 --> 14:24.125
You're very versatile.

14:24.125 --> 14:27.542
Now can we please
change the subject?

14:27.542 --> 14:29.500
Talkin' about your father...

14:29.500 --> 14:31.375
...rest his soul,
is very painful.

14:31.375 --> 14:33.083
Unh-unh. No. No.

14:33.083 --> 14:36.708
If you can talk about dad to
Travis, you can talk to me too.

14:36.708 --> 14:39.583
Well, talkin' to Travis is not
like talkin' to a real person.

14:39.583 --> 14:40.917
What?

14:40.917 --> 14:43.959
Talkin' to Travis
is like talkin' to myself.

14:43.959 --> 14:46.083
It's like when people
come into the bar

14:46.083 --> 14:49.000
and blub on and on
about their stuff

14:49.000 --> 14:52.417
I do not judge,
because I do not care.

14:52.417 --> 14:54.375
It's cheaper
than therapy for them.

14:54.375 --> 14:55.875
You think I'm gonna judge you?

14:55.875 --> 14:57.208
Marti...

14:57.208 --> 15:00.041
...everything I have
done in my life

15:00.041 --> 15:02.041
has been for your benefit.

15:02.041 --> 15:04.667
So if I don't
wanna talk about a subject

15:04.667 --> 15:06.750
you can assume
there's a good reason.

15:06.750 --> 15:09.208
He's not a subject,
he's my father.

15:09.208 --> 15:12.667
Rex was a bad guy, okay?

15:12.667 --> 15:14.708
And the only decent thing
that he has ever

15:14.708 --> 15:16.041
done in his life is supply

15:16.041 --> 15:18.625
half of your DNA,
so that the less you know...

15:18.625 --> 15:20.083
- The less you'll get hurt.
- The less I'll get hurt.

15:20.083 --> 15:22.375
You realize you say
the same damn thing

15:22.375 --> 15:24.708
every single time
I ask about dad?

15:24.708 --> 15:26.417
I-I-I didn't realize
that I was being

15:26.417 --> 15:28.250
judged for originality.

15:28.250 --> 15:30.041
It was a difficult time
in my life.

15:30.041 --> 15:31.583
I carry a lot of hurt.

15:31.583 --> 15:35.250
Did you ever consider
where I fit into this story?

15:35.250 --> 15:37.959
No, I don't even know
what story we are talking about.

15:37.959 --> 15:39.542
I will not be yelled
at in my own home.

15:39.542 --> 15:43.083
I will not
be treated like a dishrag.

15:43.083 --> 15:44.542
Not the persecution face.
I'm not falling for it.

15:44.542 --> 15:46.208
- I'm going to a movie.
- Oh, yeah?

15:46.208 --> 15:49.708
Give you a chance to calm down
from your hysteria.

15:49.708 --> 15:52.417
Eat what you want.
The food is yours.

15:52.417 --> 15:53.875
[instrumental music]

15:59.667 --> 16:01.959
[chatter]

16:03.792 --> 16:06.750
I don't see the band here yet,
so I'm gonna go to the bathroom.

16:06.750 --> 16:08.792
- Order me my usual?
- Sure.

16:08.792 --> 16:11.291
(man on microphone)
'Check one, check one, two,
three, four...'

16:11.291 --> 16:13.667
Excuse me? Hello.

16:15.166 --> 16:16.583
Excuse me.

16:16.583 --> 16:18.834
Barkeep, two whiskey
and sodas, please.

16:22.458 --> 16:26.291
- What you drinking?
- Orange juice.

16:26.291 --> 16:29.667
And an orange juice
for the lady, my fine sir.

16:31.917 --> 16:34.000
Thanks.

16:34.000 --> 16:35.291
Wait a second.
You look kinda familiar.

16:35.291 --> 16:37.917
- Do we know each other?
- Uh...

16:37.917 --> 16:40.458
Do you go to All Saints Church
on Vance Avenue?

16:40.458 --> 16:43.834
All Saints. Uh, no, uh...

16:43.834 --> 16:46.708
Not a lot of people
there that look like me.

16:46.708 --> 16:49.667
- Bald, right?
- That is exactly what I meant.

16:49.667 --> 16:51.041
Yes.

16:51.041 --> 16:52.917
Anyway, I'm bad with faces.

16:55.375 --> 16:58.208
Huh. So you like these guys?

16:58.208 --> 17:00.708
- Werewolf vs. Unicorn?
- Yeah. They're pretty cool.

17:00.708 --> 17:03.458
I saw them open
last year for Chromeo.

17:03.458 --> 17:04.500
At the New Daisy?

17:04.500 --> 17:07.000
Yeah. Were you there?

17:07.000 --> 17:08.750
Bought the bumper sticker.

17:08.750 --> 17:10.959
Wait, but are you sure these are
the guys that opened for 'em?

17:10.959 --> 17:13.000
Like I said,
"Bad with faces," but yeah.

17:13.000 --> 17:14.708
'Cause I think
I'd recognize that name.

17:14.708 --> 17:17.000
The band's been through
a bunch of different names.

17:17.000 --> 17:18.375
Yet they still ended up
with the name

17:18.375 --> 17:21.125
Werewolf vs. Unicorn.

17:21.125 --> 17:22.834
Well, the name
they had before this

17:22.834 --> 17:26.083
was "Salute the Fat Man."

17:26.083 --> 17:28.750
And before that,
they were "Sticker Shock."

17:28.750 --> 17:30.375
And for an unfortunate
two weeks

17:30.375 --> 17:32.375
they were known as "Beefeater."

17:32.375 --> 17:34.625
Ugh. That...
Unh-unh.

17:36.875 --> 17:41.041
- So here's to Unicorn and--
- Werewolf.

17:41.041 --> 17:43.208
- Werewolf versus Unicorn.
- Versus Unicorn.

17:43.208 --> 17:44.750
Alright.

17:44.750 --> 17:46.708
Clink.

17:46.708 --> 17:49.000
Mm.

17:49.000 --> 17:50.834
Well, at least,
they're danceable.

17:50.834 --> 17:52.083
Yeah, and apparently
they're good

17:52.083 --> 17:54.667
for cheerleading routines too.

17:54.667 --> 17:55.875
You're into cheerleading?

17:55.875 --> 17:57.917
Oh, I am one.

17:57.917 --> 18:01.000
- I'm Lewis, by the way.
- Oh, no.

18:01.000 --> 18:02.500
What?

18:02.500 --> 18:04.208
You're a Hellcat and...

18:04.208 --> 18:06.417
...I'm officially an idiot.

18:06.417 --> 18:10.041
Nasty Kathy. I didn't realize
it was groupie night.

18:10.041 --> 18:12.750
I would've left my bra at home.

18:12.750 --> 18:14.708
- You two know each other?
- Mm-hmm.

18:14.708 --> 18:16.917
And you're here to lobby
the band, aren't you?

18:16.917 --> 18:19.250
- Behind our backs.
- Yup.

18:19.250 --> 18:21.291
But it's gonna be much more
fun with you here

18:21.291 --> 18:23.583
watching helplessly as I take
our song away from you.

18:23.583 --> 18:24.792
Okay, ladies.

18:24.792 --> 18:26.375
Oh, she's no lady.

18:30.291 --> 18:31.583
Fraternizing with the enemy?

18:31.583 --> 18:33.417
Hey, I don't believe in enemies.

18:33.417 --> 18:35.583
- I am a lover of humanity.
- Whatever.

18:35.583 --> 18:36.625
I never met a man I didn't like.

18:36.625 --> 18:38.166
No longer listening.

18:38.166 --> 18:40.250
Yeah, I don't know if you
remember me, but...

18:40.250 --> 18:42.417
Excuse me. Um, Simon.

18:42.417 --> 18:44.417
Hi. You remember me?

18:44.417 --> 18:46.500
Uh...

18:46.500 --> 18:48.458
You gave my cheer team
permission to use your song

18:48.458 --> 18:49.458
at our national competition.

18:49.458 --> 18:51.125
Oh.

18:51.125 --> 18:53.041
- Right.
- Yeah.

18:53.041 --> 18:54.875
And you gave me
permission to use it.

18:54.875 --> 18:56.166
Yeah, 'cause I didn't
know that Simon

18:56.166 --> 18:58.083
had already given
the song to somebody else.

18:58.083 --> 18:59.792
We're on opposing teams,
you can't give us both

18:59.792 --> 19:01.458
permission to use the song.

19:01.458 --> 19:02.583
- Can't you share?
- It doesn't work like that.

19:02.583 --> 19:04.333
We don't share.

19:04.333 --> 19:06.917
We're letting you use our song.
We're not charging you anything.

19:06.917 --> 19:08.458
I don't see where
the attitude is justified.

19:08.458 --> 19:10.792
This is a nationally
televised competition.

19:10.792 --> 19:12.458
It is fantastic
exposure for your band.

19:12.458 --> 19:14.000
- Don't pretend it isn't.
- Okay, fine.

19:14.000 --> 19:15.875
But we don't care
about your politics.

19:15.875 --> 19:18.125
So y'all figure it out
for yourselves. Flip a coin.

19:18.125 --> 19:20.333
- We could do that.
- No.

19:20.333 --> 19:23.333
Simon. You gave me permission.

19:23.333 --> 19:25.834
Permission which I consider
to be exclusive.

19:25.834 --> 19:27.417
I have it in writing.

19:27.417 --> 19:29.500
- On a bar napkin.
- I bought you eight beers.

19:29.500 --> 19:31.542
- I want my money's worth.
- Fine.

19:33.500 --> 19:36.041
Here's where we rehearse.
We'll be there around 11:30.

19:36.041 --> 19:38.166
When we're done our set tonight

19:38.166 --> 19:40.750
your squad and her squad,
you're gonna show up

19:40.750 --> 19:42.166
in your hot
little cheerleader outfits

19:42.166 --> 19:43.667
and you're gonna put
on a show for us.

19:43.667 --> 19:46.375
And underwear, optional.

19:46.375 --> 19:48.959
We're not putting
on a show for you guys.

19:48.959 --> 19:50.375
And I would never
be able to assemble

19:50.375 --> 19:52.500
my entire squad
on two hours' notice.

19:52.500 --> 19:54.500
- Then you don't get the song.
- Two hours?

19:54.500 --> 19:57.166
I-I can make that happen.

19:57.166 --> 19:58.792
Okay, fine. Yeah.
We'll be there too.

19:58.792 --> 20:00.333
Pleasure doing business.

20:00.333 --> 20:04.166
- Come on, Simon.
- Underwear is optional.

20:04.166 --> 20:05.834
Seriously.

20:05.834 --> 20:09.500
Hey, Alice, good luck
tracking down your squad.

20:09.500 --> 20:11.834
Mine are all in the same
youth group meeting.

20:13.417 --> 20:14.750
[snorts]

20:17.375 --> 20:20.083
- How'd it go?
- We have to call everyone.

20:20.083 --> 20:21.875
We need them in uniform
and ready to cheer.

20:23.166 --> 20:24.917
[instrumental music]

20:24.917 --> 20:26.250
[cell phone ringing]

20:36.500 --> 20:38.708
I was messed up after
that night in the movie theater.

20:38.708 --> 20:39.917
I needed someone to talk to

20:39.917 --> 20:41.834
and nobody knows you
like Charlotte.

20:44.250 --> 20:49.083
So you went to talk to my sister
about me and slept with her.

20:50.750 --> 20:53.125
When you lay it out like that,
it sounds sketchy.

20:53.125 --> 20:54.291
Gee, Noah, you think?

20:54.291 --> 20:56.208
I'm not proud of what I did.

20:56.208 --> 20:58.250
I strayed from my path,
but I deserve a little credit

20:58.250 --> 20:59.834
for trying to do
the right thing now.

21:01.417 --> 21:02.458
Do you love her?

21:03.583 --> 21:04.875
I offered to marry her.

21:06.041 --> 21:07.959
You didn't answer the question.

21:11.583 --> 21:13.750
- I love you.
- Oh, Noah, don't do this.

21:13.750 --> 21:16.875
No. Everything I said
in that movie theater was true.

21:16.875 --> 21:18.875
We can make it work between us.
I know we can.

21:18.875 --> 21:20.458
Stop.

21:20.458 --> 21:21.875
I'm sorry.

21:23.417 --> 21:26.208
I know my timing
is really bad.

21:26.208 --> 21:28.750
But I just feel...like this
could be my last chance

21:28.750 --> 21:31.458
to tell you how I feel.

21:31.458 --> 21:35.625
I've never stopped loving you,
and I never will.

21:35.625 --> 21:39.458
In three months, you will
have a wife and a baby.

21:39.458 --> 21:40.792
I will be your
sister-in-law.

21:40.792 --> 21:43.291
It doesn't have to be like that.

21:43.291 --> 21:45.750
Noah, nothing will ever happen

21:45.750 --> 21:48.500
with you and me. Okay?

21:48.500 --> 21:52.625
That night in the movie theater,
I obviously gave you false hope.

21:52.625 --> 21:55.208
I'm sorry for that.

21:55.208 --> 21:58.125
But the idea of us
running off together

21:58.125 --> 22:01.625
especially in light
of all this, well...

22:01.625 --> 22:03.583
That's just
an immature fantasy.

22:05.125 --> 22:06.792
You're acting like a child.

22:08.417 --> 22:10.083
I see.

22:12.250 --> 22:14.417
Well, then all you have
to do is say the word.

22:15.834 --> 22:17.458
The word, what word?

22:17.458 --> 22:19.917
Tell me you want me
to marry Charlotte and I will.

22:22.000 --> 22:23.667
Oh, my gosh.

22:24.875 --> 22:26.291
Wow.

22:28.291 --> 22:30.667
You got yourself
into this situation.

22:30.667 --> 22:32.875
You and Charlotte.

22:32.875 --> 22:36.333
So whatever you decide to do
about it is your responsibility.

22:36.333 --> 22:38.625
And trying to make
it my responsibility...

22:38.625 --> 22:41.458
...I'm sorry, Noah, but that's
a really crappy thing to do.

22:41.458 --> 22:42.917
Savannah?

22:45.792 --> 22:47.166
Goodbye, Noah.

22:55.458 --> 22:57.375
I can't believe
you finally got into Lancer.

22:57.375 --> 22:59.041
Hm. Thanks for the
vote of confidence.

22:59.041 --> 23:01.834
Well, you know what I mean.
It's exciting.

23:01.834 --> 23:03.500
You have any idea what
the film project's gonna be?

23:03.500 --> 23:06.000
The assignment
is to...make a trailer.

23:06.000 --> 23:07.542
I need a concept that's bold.

23:07.542 --> 23:09.834
You know, something
that shows I can move a camera.

23:09.834 --> 23:11.875
But I don't have
any money to work with.

23:11.875 --> 23:13.500
Sounds like suspense or horror.

23:13.500 --> 23:14.708
That's what I was thinking.

23:14.708 --> 23:16.000
Best ones are done
on the cheap.

23:16.000 --> 23:17.750
You wanna be in it?

23:17.750 --> 23:20.000
Only if you promise me
a blood-soaked, gory death.

23:20.000 --> 23:21.208
What are best friends for?

23:21.208 --> 23:23.667
I wanna see
my own intestines.

23:23.667 --> 23:25.792
- Lower, upper?
- Lower.

23:25.792 --> 23:27.708
I've been doing some sculpting
on my lower GI tract.

23:27.708 --> 23:31.041
- I wanna show it off.
- Vanity, thy name is woman.

23:31.041 --> 23:33.041
'Consider it done.'

23:33.041 --> 23:35.542
[cell phone ringing]

23:35.542 --> 23:37.208
Who is that,
your drug dealer?

23:37.208 --> 23:40.917
Mm. Alice.
Whatever she wants can wait.

23:44.917 --> 23:46.834
So dad's song...

23:48.875 --> 23:50.750
How was it?

23:53.875 --> 23:55.959
It was fine.

23:55.959 --> 23:57.917
The sheet music displayed
impeccable penmanship

23:57.917 --> 23:59.625
which apparently
I didn't inherit.

23:59.625 --> 24:01.959
Well, God rarely
gives with both hands.

24:06.458 --> 24:10.375
I've known you a long time.
You know that?

24:10.375 --> 24:12.208
Obviously.

24:12.208 --> 24:16.875
When you decide to accomplish
something, M, you go after it.

24:16.875 --> 24:18.333
Guns blazing.

24:19.291 --> 24:20.834
You do.

24:22.417 --> 24:25.917
If you wanted to know
about your dad, I mean...

24:25.917 --> 24:28.166
Wanda's never been
capable of stopping you.

24:28.166 --> 24:29.417
Your point?

24:29.417 --> 24:32.291
And if this means
so much to you...

24:32.291 --> 24:34.000
...why didn't you push harder?

24:39.834 --> 24:41.792
That's a good question.

24:43.959 --> 24:46.208
I was in eighth grade,
I think.

24:47.667 --> 24:50.375
And I, I asked
why they split up.

24:53.792 --> 24:56.917
She didn't want to talk
about it, but I kept pushing.

24:56.917 --> 24:59.834
No matter what she said,
I wouldn't let it go.

25:02.667 --> 25:05.500
She ends up in tears,
the bottle comes out

25:05.500 --> 25:09.041
she starts calling herself
a bad mom... Blah blah blah.

25:09.041 --> 25:11.667
Hitting herself in the face.

25:11.667 --> 25:14.667
Finally, I carried her
off to bed

25:14.667 --> 25:18.083
which is where she ended up
staying for the next week.

25:18.083 --> 25:22.333
I had to call her work and make
up some BS story about the flu.

25:26.166 --> 25:28.250
At the end of the day,
it just wasn't...

25:28.250 --> 25:30.000
...wasn't worth
the hassle, you know?

25:31.333 --> 25:33.125
Yeah, I guess not.

25:37.834 --> 25:39.667
She's known Travis
for two and a half minutes

25:39.667 --> 25:41.917
and she's spilling
her guts to him.

25:45.375 --> 25:46.708
That hurts.

25:46.708 --> 25:48.125
[instrumental music]

25:50.041 --> 25:51.417
[cell phone beeps]

25:53.667 --> 25:55.667
- It's not Alice, is it?
- No, it's Savannah.

25:55.667 --> 25:58.708
She's looking for you, actually.
Says it's an emergency.

26:00.708 --> 26:03.500
[chatter]

26:08.708 --> 26:09.875
Is Charlotte here yet?

26:09.875 --> 26:11.708
Not yet,
but thank God you guys are.

26:11.708 --> 26:13.208
- Are you ready?
- Yeah.

26:13.208 --> 26:16.834
You ladies wearing underwear?

26:16.834 --> 26:18.625
You guys wearing a dunce cap?

26:18.625 --> 26:20.667
You should be.
You're underdressed without it.

26:23.083 --> 26:25.542
Touche.

26:25.542 --> 26:27.792
That dude's stoned.

26:27.792 --> 26:29.625
Why are we cheering
for these creeps again?

26:29.625 --> 26:32.583
We have to,
or we lose the song.

26:32.583 --> 26:35.917
Li'l Kim's looking pretty
attractive right about now.

26:35.917 --> 26:38.291
Alright, let's get this
party started. Who's first?

26:39.375 --> 26:42.208
["Hot To Touch"]

